SIMPLE: gride
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gride
<hw>Gride</hw> <pr>(gr⟦imac⟧d)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Grided</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Griding</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[For gird, properly, to strike
with a rod. See <er>Yard</er> a measure, and cf. <er>Grid</er> to
strike, sneer.]</ety> <def>To cut with a grating sound; to cut; to
penetrate or pierce harshly; <as>as, the <ex>griding</ex>
sword</as>.</def> <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That through his thigh the mortal steel did <qex>gride</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gride</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Gride
<hw>Gride</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A harsh scraping or cutting; a
grating.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>gride</qex> of hatchets fiercely thrown.⟦br⟧
On wigwam log, and tree, and stone.</q>
<rj><qau>Whittier.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gridelin</ent>⟦br⟧
